<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About Us - 404 Brain Not Found</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <style>
   

    .about-page {
      padding-top: 50px;  
      margin: 30px auto;
      max-width: 1000px;
      padding: 20px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1f1c2c, #928dab);
      background-size: 400% 400%;
      animation: gradientBG 15s ease infinite;
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
    }

    @keyframes gradientBG {
      0%   { background-position: 0% 50%; }
      50%  { background-position: 100% 50%; }
      100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
    }
 /* Heading */
    .about-page h1 {
      font-size: 3.5rem;
      color: #ff4c68;
      text-shadow: 2px 2px #000;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      animation: float 3s infinite alternate;
    }

    @keyframes float {
      0%   { transform: translateY(0px); }
      100% { transform: translateY(-10px); }
    }

    /* Joke cards */
    .joke {
      position: relative;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      margin: 20px auto;
      padding: 20px 30px;
      border-radius: 15px;
      width: 90%;
      max-width: 700px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .joke:hover {
      transform: scale(1.03);
      background: rgba(0, 255, 234, 0.15);
      box-shadow: 0 0 35px rgba(0, 255, 234, 0.5);
    }

    .joke::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: -50%;
      left: -50%;
      width: 200%;
      height: 200%;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2) 0%, transparent 60%);
      transform: rotate(45deg);
      animation: shine 3s infinite linear;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    @keyframes shine {
      0%   { transform: translate(-100%, -100%) rotate(45deg); }
      100% { transform: translate(100%, 100%) rotate(45deg); }
    }

    .joke p {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin: 8px 0;
      color: #fff;
    }

    /* Responsive */
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .about-page h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; }
      .joke p { font-size: 1rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Navbar -->
 {{>navbar}}

  <!-- About Page -->
  <div class="about-page">
    <h1>About Us 🤓</h1>

    <!-- 10× Core Jokes -->
    <div class="joke">
      <p>💻 Why do programmers prefer dark mode?</p>
      <p>Because the light attracts bugs. 🐛</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🧠 Warning: Low memory... <br>Would you like to close Stack Overflow?</p>
      <p>No. I’d rather close my career. 😭</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🔧 My code doesn’t have bugs—it just develops random features.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🛠️ Debugging: Being the detective in a crime movie where you are also the murderer.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>☠️ SQL query walks into a bar, walks up to two tables and asks: “Can I JOIN you?”</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🧟‍♂️ If at first you don’t succeed... call it version 1.0.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>😵 Tried to solve a bug for 3 hours… Gave up and wrote “Works on my machine.”</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🐒 A coder’s spirit animal is a rubber duck—because it listens to all your problems.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>📚 Always comment your code—one day you’ll thank yourself (or your grave).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="joke">
      <p>🚀 Remember: In space, no one can hear you semicolon.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer -->
  {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>
